"Salati E., Nobre C.A., Dos Santos A.A.","Amazonian deforestation: Regional and global issues",2001,"Amazoniana","16","3-4",,"463","481",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0039782321&partnerID=40&md5=53eccbcb5a50dbd0c51af6e861f4d55e","Fund. o Desenvolvimento Sustentavel, Rua Golf Club 115, 2610-040 Rio de Janeiro/RJ, Brazil; Ctro. Previsao Tempo Estud. C., Rodovia Presidente Dutra, Km 40, 12630-000 Cachoeira Paulista/SP, Brazil","Salati, E., Fund. o Desenvolvimento Sustentavel, Rua Golf Club 115, 2610-040 Rio de Janeiro/RJ, Brazil; Nobre, C.A., Ctro. Previsao Tempo Estud. C., Rodovia Presidente Dutra, Km 40, 12630-000 Cachoeira Paulista/SP, Brazil; Dos Santos, A.A., Fund. o Desenvolvimento Sustentavel, Rua Golf Club 115, 2610-040 Rio de Janeiro/RJ, Brazil","How does the deforestation of Amazonia affect global and regional climates? What are the roles of these changes on Amazonian ecosystems? We have concluded that the relation between Regional Climate Changes (RCC) and Global Climate Change (GCC) is directly associated with anthropogenic activities and therefore sensitive to social, economical and political interventions. The RCCs are caused by actions within the realm of the Brazilian sociopolitical scenario, and prone to changes through the implementation of public policies regulating the sustained use of the renewable resources. The GCCs belong to an international arena, and are caused by the high emission rates of greenhouse gases by the developed countries. The effects of the RCCs could be abated if the developed countries would endeavor to reduce the present emission levels as documented in IPCC meetings and collaborate in the implementation of a regulation to curb the carbon emissions, in accordance to the Kyoto Protocol.","Amazon; Carbon; Climate change; Deforestation; Emission; Global change; Neotropics",,,,,,,"Carter, T., Hulme, M., Interim characterizations of regional climate and related changes up to 2100 (2000) Associates with the Provisional Sres Marker Emissions -Scenarios, , IPCC Secretariat. WMO, Geneva; Gash, J.H.C., Nobre, C.A., Climatic effects of Amazonian deforestation: Some results from ABRACOS (1997) Bull. Amer. Meteorol. Soc., 78 (5), pp. 823-830; Gash, J.H.C., Nobre, C.A., Roberts, J.M., Victoria, R.L., Conclusions from ABRACOS (1996) Amazonian Deforestation and Climate, , GASH, J.H.C., NOBRE, C.A., ROBERTS, J.M. & R.L. VICTORIA (eds.): 577-96. John Wiley & Sons Ltd., New York: 611 pp; Hammond, A.L., (1993) World Resources 1992-93. A Report, , The World Resources Institute. Oxford University Press, New York: 385 pp; Climate change - Contributions of working groups (1995) IPCC - Intergovernamental Panel on Climate Change, , Cambridge University Press; (2000) Emissions Scenarios - IPCC Special Report, , IPCC Secretariat. WMO, Geneva; Marques, J., Salati, E., Santos, J.M., Cálculo da evapotranspiração real na bacia amazônica através do método aerologico (1980) Acta Amazônica, 10 (2), pp. 357-361; Marques, J., Salati, E., Santos, J.M., A divergência do campo do fluxo de vapor d'água e as chuvas na região amazônica (1980) Acta Amazônica, 10 (1), pp. 133-140; Myers, N., Mittermeier, R.A., Mittermeier, C.G., Da Fonseca, G.A.B., Kent, J., Biodiversity hotspots for conservation priorities 2000 (2000) Nature, 403, pp. 853-858; Nepstad, D.C., Veríssimo, A., Alencar, A., Nobre, C., Lima, E., Lefebvre, P., Schlesinger, P., Brooks, V., Large scale improverishment of Amazonian forests by logging and fire (1999) Nature, 398, pp. 505-508; Nobre, C.A., Selllers, P., Shukla, J., Regional climate change and Amazonian deforestation model (1991) J. Climate, 4 (10), pp. 957-988; Pimm, L.S., Raven, P., Extinctions by numbers (2000) Nature, 403, pp. 843-845; Salati, E., The climatology and hydrology of Amazonia (1985) Amazonia: 18-48, , PergamonPress,Oxford:442pp, PRANCE, G.T. & T.E. LOVEJOY (eds.); Salati, E., Marques, J., Climatology of the Amazon region (1984) The Amazon - Limnology and Landscape Ecolo